Addie McPhail https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addie_McPhail 0 Addie McPhail (July 15, 1905 – April 14, 2003) was an American film actress. She appeared in 64 films between 1927 and 1941. She was the third and last wife of Roscoe "Fatty" Arbuckle. After she retired from acting, she served for 17 years as a volunteer nurse at the Motion Picture Television Country House and Hospital in Woodland Hills, California.
